Details:
Article 382 stipulates that a state functionary who, by taking advantage of his position, appropriates, steals, defrauds or otherwise illegally takes possession of public property shall be convicted of the crime of embezzlement. A person who is entrusted by a state organ, a state-owned company, enterprise, public institution or people's organization to manage or operate state-owned property and who, by taking advantage of his position, appropriates, steals, defrauds or otherwise illegally takes possession of state-owned property shall be deemed to have committed the crime of embezzlement. A person who colludes with the persons mentioned in the preceding two paragraphs to commit embezzlement shall be regarded as a joint offender.

Whoever commits the crime of embezzlement shall be punished in accordance with the following provisions based on the seriousness of the circumstances:
(1) If the amount involved is relatively large or the circumstances are relatively serious, he shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not more than three years or criminal detention and shall also be fined;
(2) If the amount involved is huge or the circumstances are serious, he shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than three years but not more than ten years and shall also be fined or have his property confiscated;
(3) If the amount involved is especially huge or the circumstances are especially serious, he shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than ten years or life imprisonment and shall also be fined or have his property confiscated; if the amount involved is especially huge and causes especially major losses to the interests of the state and the people, he shall be sentenced to life imprisonment or death and shall also have his property confiscated.

Article 263 stipulates that whoever robs public or private property by means of violence, coercion or other methods shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than three years but not more than ten years and shall also be fined; whoever commits any of the following acts shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than ten years, life imprisonment or death and shall also be fined or have his property confiscated:
(1) Robbing a residence;
(2) Robbing on a public transportation vehicle;
(3) Robbing a bank or any other financial institution;
(4) Committing robbery many times or robbing a huge amount of property;
(5) Robbery causing serious injury or death to a person;
(6) Robbing while posing as a military or police officer;
(7) Robbing with a gun;
(8) Robbing military materials or materials for emergency rescue, disaster relief or poverty alleviation.

Article 267 stipulates that whoever assembles a crowd to engage in affrays shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not more than three years, criminal detention or public surveillance for the ringleaders and other active participants; if any of the following circumstances exists, the ringleaders and other active participants shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than three years but not more than ten years:
(1) Engaging in affrays many times;
(2) Engaging in affrays with a large number of people, on a large scale and with a bad social impact;
(3) Engaging in affrays in a public place or at a traffic artery, causing serious disruption to public order;
(4) Engaging in affrays with weapons.

Whoever engages in affrays leading to serious injury or death of a person shall be convicted and punished in accordance with the provisions of Articles 234 and 232 of this Law.

Article 236 stipulates that whoever rapes a woman by means of violence, coercion or other methods shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than three years but not more than ten years.

Whoever has sexual intercourse with a girl under the age of 14 shall be deemed to have committed rape and shall be given a heavier punishment.

Whoever rapes a woman or has sexual intercourse with a girl under the age of 14 and commits any of the following acts shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than ten years, life imprisonment or death:
(1) Committing rape or having sexual intercourse with a girl under the age of 14 in especially serious circumstances;
(2) Raping many women or having sexual intercourse with many girls under the age of 14;
(3) Raping a woman or having sexual intercourse with a girl under the age of 14 in a public place in the presence of others;
(4) Raping a woman together with another person or persons (gang rape);
(5) Having sexual intercourse with a girl under the age of 10 or causing injury to a girl under the age of 14;
(6) Causing serious injury or death to the victim or other serious consequences.
